JOHANNESBURG A shortage of steering parts has led BMW to halt production in South Africa.Production at BMW's Rosslyn plant near Pretoria will likely stop for 24 hours because an unidentified Italian car-parts supplier has been unable to deliver the required parts.READ: General Motors exits SA - Isuzu to step inThe company's Leipzig site in Germany has been closed since Friday and another facility in Munich was affected last week.A plant in China has also been shut down.BMW's Rosslyn plant manufactures 3-series models.eNCA